To resolve this error, you need to install the @types/bson package because the TypeScript compiler needs type definitions for bson in order to recognize the ObjectId type.

To install the package, run the following command in your terminal:

```
npm install @types/bson
```

Then, import the ObjectId type from the bson package in your React component:

```
import { ObjectId } from 'bson';
```

You can now use the ObjectId type in your component without encountering the TypeScript error:

```
interface MyProps {
  id: ObjectId;
}

function MyComponent({ id }: MyProps) {
  // ...
}
```

